 in public health, epidemiology, or related field. • Seven years’ experience specifically related to project/program management. • At least three years of supervisory/personnel management experience. • Strong professional oral and written communication skills; and the ability to interact with both internal staff and external customers. • Prior experience in donor and partner relations, particularly, experience working with the CDCStrong interpersonal and intercultural skills • Previous experience working on international projects • Proficiency with Microsoft Office applications (Excel, Word, Outlook, PowerPoint, etc.) NOTE: This role will be granted the opportunity to work from home temporarily during the COVID-19 pandemic, with intent to return to an Emory University location in the future. Emory reserves the right to change remote work status with notice to employee. Emory Supports a Diverse and Inclusive Culture To ensure the safety of our campus community, the COVID-19 vaccine is required. For more information on the University and Hospital policies and potential exemptions, please see our website. Emory University is dedicated to providing equal opportunities and equal access to all individuals regardless of race, color, religion, ethnic or national origin, gender, genetic information, age, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, and veteran\'s status. Emory University does not discriminate in admissions, educational programs, or employment on the basis of any factor stated above or prohibited under applicable law. Students, faculty, and staff are assured of participation in University programs and in the use of facilities without such discrimination. Emory University complies with Executive Order 11246, as amended, Section 503 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, the Vietnam Era Veteran\'s Readjustment Assistance Act, and applicable executive orders, federal and state regulations regarding nondiscrimination, equal opportunity and affirmative action. Emory University is committed to achieving a diverse workforce through application of its affirmative action, equal opportunity and nondiscrimination policy in all aspects of employment including recruitment, hiring, promotions, transfers, discipline, terminations, wage and salary administration, benefits, and training. Inquiries regarding this policy should be directed to the Emory University Department of Equity and Inclusion, 201 Dowman Drive, Administration Building, Atlanta, GA 30322. Emory University is committed to providing reasonable accommodations to qualified individuals with disabilities upon request. To request this document in an alternate format or to request a reasonable accommodation, please contact the Department of Accessibility Services at 404-727-9877 (V) | 404-712-2049 (TDD). Please note that one week advance notice is preferred', '2022-03-03 00:00:00', 'Georgia', '9.0', 'Full Time', '2022-03-03 00:00:00', 'Job Poster', 'web.com', 'company.com', 'It is a long established fact that a reader will b...', 'assets/img/icon/job-list1.png'),
('9.0', 'Physician / Urology / Georgia / Permanent / Urologist Needed in Central...', '2500usd', 'https://hypjobs.com/job-zt/ceb584e2def74a867722834407f101a1/Physician-Urology-Georgia-Permanent-Urologist-Needed-in-Central-Georgia-Job/Warner-Robins/GA?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'Job Description CompHealth is currently assisting a Georgia hospital with their search for a urologist Join an existing group with a partnership track that will require no buy-in or be employed by the hospital. There is 1 other urologist that is planning to retire or go to part time in the next few years. Your call schedule will be 1:2 during the week and 1:6 weekends. You will need to be board certified and fellowship trained. This position will require a GA license, and CompHealth has a licensing team that can help you with the process and application. This position offers an income guarantee for 2 years with an RVU bonus and a quality bonus. You will also receive a hospital supported student loan repayment options up to $100K, a generous commencement bonus, full comprehensive benefits for you and your family, up to $15K relocation assistance, life insurance plan, a 403b and 457b retirement plans, CME allowance, and malpractice insurance with tail coverage. You will enjoy living and working in this large Georgia town. You will be surrounded by wooded countryside, while still having access to larger metropolitan amenities in nearby of Macon, GA, and Atlanta, GA. The area has affordable homes, an interesting history, and excellent Southern music and eating establishments. Our goal is to ensure that your interaction with us is seamless and stress-free from start to finish. Every step of the way, you\'ll be supported by specialty teams comprised of tenured professionals with decades of collective experience finding urologist jobs. To begin talking about this position, contact Trevor Jensen at 801.930.3776 or email your CV and references to t