('14.0', 'Purchasing Agent- The Providence Group of Georgia', '2500usd', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/purchasing-agent-the-providence-group-of-georgia-at-green-brick-partners-inc-2910987294/?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'The Purchasing Agent must believe in, practice and initiate all Green Brick Partners values set forth in an acronym we call HOME. They must be Honest, Objective, Mature and Efficient in how he or she approaches their role at Green Brick Partners Responsible for entering into negotiations with suppliers by reviewing terms and conditions, contract formulation, and any supplier management conditions affecting the division. Responsibilities: • Complete estimates of costs and quantities of residential products using comparative and differential estimating techniques. • Performs analysis of Trade Partner data submissions and manages impact of commodity fluctuations • Maintain all applicable databases (Takeoffs, Newstar, etc.) used in developing the cost and quantity estimates • Complete necessary customer pricing requests • Communicate completed estimates to the construction personnel, trade subcontractors and vendors • Check and verify all completed estimates through field verifications and the prototype process, focusing on quantities • Provide accurate and timely local supplier contracting based on defined category selection criteria i.e., cost quality, productivity, service) • Manage supplier performance monitoring within the division (i.e., cost, quality, productivity, service) • Manage compliance to agreement, scopes, Etc. • Manage and execute contract agreements consistent with sourcing guidelines • Manage supplier relationships and assist in resolving issues and conflicts related to daily Trade Partner Activities • Collaborate with Construction to update and maintain building schedule in Newstar Supervision of Others: N/A Authority/Budget/Decision Making/Discretion and Independent Judgment