('46.0', 'Security Operations Specialist', '2500usd', 'https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/security-operations-specialist-at-ups-2927922526?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'The Security Operations Center Specialist is part of a 24x7 security threat and data review that will receive and disseminate immediate threats to relevant management and employees. This position will assist in the development and dissemination of UPS responses to security directives. The individual will develop and help maintain appropriate internal and external contacts around the world. This position will develop communication agreements with law enforcement and government agencies. The Security Operations Center Specialist assists the internal security web page for the field that provides a centralized reference of relevant internal and external security related contact information. He/she maintains comprehensive contact list of key internal and external (e.g., Transportation Security Administration, Department of State, FBI, etc.) contacts to ensure a thorough and consistent communication of security-related information. This position assists the management team in all areas of the UPS enterprise regarding security-related circumstances to communicate perceived threats to UPS. Other Duties • Manages database (i.e., Incident Reporting System) to determine proactive measures to be taken to address emerging threats. • Provides assistance in the development and dissemination of UPS responses to security directives. • Monitors database usage to ensure high levels of database performance. • Develops communication agreements with law enforcement and government agencies. • Assembles background information and facts about accidents and crises to ensure that UPS responds to information requests appropriately. • Gathers and analyzes preliminary data for management team to help determine strategic direction for communications (e.g., reactive, proactive, limited or full disclosure, etc.) to maintain UPS’s positive public image during a crisis. • Analyzes and creates technical written documents that summarize security intelligence. Preferred Competencies • Identifies the business problem that requires research; identifies sources of information that are relevant to a problem; reviews literature and data related to the research question; summarizes information from data sources. • Captures/documents specific and accurate information; learns subjects thoroughly and in detail; completes work with thoroughness; supplies appropriate details when requested; maintains organized files. • Describes types of incidents; demonstrates basic knowledge of requirements for initiating an investigation of incidents; describes the procedures followed for investigating incidents. • Demonstrates a basic understanding of the functions, regulations, and procedures of compliance agencies or governing bodies; takes a leadership position in programs that reduce risk and enhance safety. • Demonstrates a basic knowledge of risk management fundamentals. • Demonstrates a general knowledge of techniques for soliciting and gathering information. • Demonstrates a general understanding of technology used by the company; communicates basic technological concepts and terminology; applies standard technology in daily work. MINIMUM QUALIFIERS • Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Industrial Engineering, Information Systems, Communications, Criminal Justice, Law Enforcement, Business Administration, Political Science, Journalism, or History- Preferred UPS is an equal opportunity employer. UPS does not discriminate on the basis of race/color/religion/sex/national origin/veteran/disability/age/sexual orientation/gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law', '2022-04-10 00:00:00', 'Georgia', '20.0', 'Full Time', '2022-04-10 00:00:00', 'Job Poster', 'web.com', 'company.com', 'It is a long established fact that a reader will b...', 'assets/i