('55.0', 'Physician / Family Practice / Georgia / Permanent / IM or FM Physician...', '2500usd', 'https://localjobs.fox8jobs.com/jobs/physician-family-practice-georgia-permanent-im-or-fm-physician-opportunity-in-georgia-job-near-the-s/498590217-2/?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'A primary care clinic in Georgia needs an additional family practice, internal medicine, med-ped, or geriatric medicine physician. The clinic is open from 8 am to 7 pm Monday through Thursday, and 8 am to 12 pm on Friday. The incoming physician will work 40 hours per week evaluating and treating a wide range of illnesses and injuries. There will be a shared outpatient call. Evaluate and treat a wide range of illnesses and injuries. Procedures include joint injections, minor dermatology, and office-based procedures. The facility requires that you be board certified, or board eligible if you are taking the boards or are less than 2 years out of your residency. H-1B visas are welcome to apply. This hospital-employed position offers a generous compensation package and bonuses. You will also receive relocation assistance, a sign-on bonus, medical/dental/vision benefits, 4 weeks of PTO, life insurance/disability, 2 weeks of CME time, a 403(b) retirement plan, and occurrence malpractice coverage. Come live and practice in a beautiful part of Georgia near the South Carolina boarder that has plenty of outdoor recreation, mouthwatering culinary experiences, and access to the beaches on weekends. If this opportunity sounds interesting to you, contact your personal CompHealth consultant for more information about this position and to discuss other jobs that fit your life, your goals, and your schedule. To get started, call Linda Jacovino directly at 203.663.9350 or email your CV and references in confidence to linda.jacovino@. Established and busy practice Monday through Friday, 4.5-day workweek, 40 hours per week Share outpatient call with other physicians Support includes CMA, NP, PA, and clinical leads Full sub-specialty support available BC or BE if a resident Great benefits offered Occurrence malpractice coverage Our services are free for you We help negotiate your salary and contract We coordinate interviews and help with licenses Specialized recruiters match your career preferences Experienced support teams take care of every detail', '2022-04-19 00:00:00', 'Georgia', '20.0', 'Freelance', '2022-04-19 00:00:00', 'Job Poster', 'web.com', 'company.com', 'It is a long established fact that a reader will b...', 'assets/img/icon/job-list1.png');
