are of children under the age of 18 or direct patient care?: No Does this position have Security Access (e.g., public safety, IT security, personnel records, patient records, or access to chemicals and medications): No Credit and P-Card policy: Be advised a credit check will be required for all positions with financial responsibilities. For additional information about the credit check criteria, visit the UGA Credit Background Check website. Duties/Responsibilities: Provide independent assistance and support for UGA extension programs, including answering Extension Agent calls and e-mails, Agent training, Agent resource development, and specialized training of an Agent team focused on fisheries. Percentage of time: 40 Duties/Responsibilities: Create and maintain databases, perform data analysis, create spatial and temporal data visualization applications for various research and outreach projects. Percentage of time: 20 Duties/Responsibilities: Develop grant proposals, technical reports, and manuscripts for research and outreach publications. Utilize research data to create web tools such as ArcGIS StoryMaps for outreach projects. Percentage of time: 20 Duties/Responsibilities: Independent planning, logistics and implementation of field data collection missions for various research and outreach projects. Will plan and carryout field work according to established protocols in order to ensure safe and successful outcomes. Changing conditions (weather, equipment, etc..) will at times involve independent decision-making during travel to remote locations. Percentage of time: 20 Contact Details: For questions concerning this position or recruitment progression, please refer to the Recruitment Contact listed below. Recruitment Contact Name: Jay Shelton Recruitment Contact Email: jshelton@uga.edu Recruitment Contact Phone: 706-542-2686', '2022-04-30 00:00:00', 'Georgia', '20.0', 'Freelance', '2022-04-30 00:00:00', 'Job Poster', 'web.com', 'company.com', 'It is a long establ