er requirements in terms of content, quality, delivery, sustainability and price. Your background • Bachelor’s degree, preferably in Supply Chain, Business Administration or related, and minimum 8 years of experience in Supply Chain field, project management, OR Associate\'s Degree, and minimum 10 years of experience in Supply Chain field, project management. • Open to travel 20% local and international. • Candidates must already have a work authorization that would permit them to work for ABB in the USA. • Preferred Qualifications: Demonstrated experience working with enterprise resource planning and standard operating procedures required. • Experience in supply base supporting robotics, logistics, healthcare/medical devices, food & beverage, and packaging markets. • Desired SCM Certification; CPSM, CPIM, CSCP. Knowledge of SAP and MS Office (Word, Excel, etc.) is highly preferred. • A collaborative, solution-focused approach and strong written and spoken communication skills preferred. Benefits • Retirement plan • Life insurance • Disability insurance • Medical insurance • Wellbeing program More about us ABB Robotics & Discrete Automation is a pioneer in robotics, machine automation and digital services, providing innovative solutions for a diverse range of industries, from automotive to electronics to logistics. As one of the world’s leading robotics and machine automation suppliers, we have shipped over 500,000 robot solutions. We help our customers of all sizes to increase productivity, flexibility and simplicity and to improve output quality. We support their transition towards the connected and collaborative factory of the future. ABB Robotics & Discrete Automation employs more than 11,000 people at over 100 locations in more than 53 countries. www.abb.com/robotics We look forward to receiving your application. If you want to discover more about ABB, take another look at our website www.abb.com. Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action at ABB ABB i