('102.0', 'Animal Facilities Supervisor-FRS/ADS Alapaha', '2500usd', 'https://careers.insidehighered.com/job/2394381/animal-facilities-supervisor-frsads-alapaha?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'Posting Number: S07915P Working Title: Animal Facilities Supervisor-FRS/ADS Alapaha Department: CAES-Animal & Dairy Science About the University of Georgia: PLEASE NOTE: On December 7, 2021, the federal District Court for the Southern District of Georgia issued a preliminary injunction against enforcing the vaccine requirement for Federal Contractors pending further review. As a result, the requirements of the Executive Order and associated guidance, including the vaccination requirement for covered contractor employees, are currently not in effect. The University of Georgia (UGA), a land-grant and sea-grant university with statewide commitments and responsibilities, is the state’s oldest, most comprehensive, and most diversified institution of higher education (https://www.uga.edu/). UGA is currently ranked among the top 15 public universities in U.S. News & World Report. The University’s main campus is located in Athens, approximately 65 miles northeast of Atlanta, with extended campuses in Atlanta, Griffin, Gwinnett, and Tifton. UGA was founded in 1785 by the Georgia General Assembly as the first state-chartered University in the country. UGA employs approximately 1,800 full-time instructional faculty and more than 7,700 full-time staff. The University’s enrollment exceeds 39,000 students including over 30,000 undergraduates and over 9,000 graduate and professional students. Academic programs reside in 18 schools and colleges, as well as a medical partnership with Augusta University housed on the UGA Health Sciences Campus in Athens. About the College/Unit/Department: In 2018, The UGA Tifton Campus began a yearlong Centennial celebration with various events to commemorate its 100th anniversary of providing updated research to the community. Research is done on a wide range of commodities, including cotton, peanuts, vegetables and turf grass, all of which make agriculture the No. 1 industry in Georgia. In 2004, a teaching program was initiated and it has been growing ever since. College-level instruction on campus is aimed at undergraduate and graduate-degree level study. College/Unit/Department website: http://www.caes.uga.edu/campuses/tifton/about/administrative-offices/field-research-services.html Posting Type: External Retirement Plan: TRS Employment Type: Employee Benefits Eligibility: Benefits Eligible Full/Part time: Full Time Additional Schedule Information: Schedule to be determined by supervisor Advertised Salary: Commensurate with education, experience and training Posting Date: 02/16/2022 Open until filled: Yes Proposed Starting Date: 03/14/2022 Special Instructions to Applicants: This position is located in Tifton, GA, which is approximately 200 miles southwest of Athens, Georgia, 200 miles south of Atlanta, GA and approximately 70 miles north of the Florida line. Location of Vacancy: Tifton Area EEO Policy Statement: The University of Georgia is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, ethnicity, age, genetic information, disability, gender identity, sexual orientation or protected veteran status. Persons needing accommodations or assistance with the accessibility of materials related to this search are encouraged to contact Central HR (hrweb@uga.edu). UGA Statement: PLEASE NOTE: On December 7, 2021, the federal District Court for the Southern District of Georgia issued a preliminary injunction against enforcing the vaccine requirement for Federal Contractors pending further review. As a result, the requirements of the Executive Order and associated guidance, including the vaccination requirement for covered contractor employees, are currently not in effect. The University of Georgia is a Federal Contractor as defined by Presidential Executive Order 14042 and subject to the requirement that Federal Contractors must ensure that all covered employees, including those working remotely, are fully vaccinated by January 4, 2022. You may be required to show proof of your fully vaccinated status at the time of your start date, or have received a medical or religious exemption from the fully vaccinated requirement at the time of your start date. For more information regarding the Federal Contractor fully vaccinated employment requirement please visit https://coronavirus.uga.edu/executive-order/ or call (706) 542-2222. Classification Title: Facility Operations Paraprofessional/Professional FLSA: Non-Exempt Job Family: Agriculture FTE: 1.00 Minimum Qualifications: Requires technical knowledge in the field acquired through an apprenticeship, a 2-year degree, or professional certificate. Please contact your Human Resources office for an evaluation of education/experience in lieu of the required minimum qualifications. Preferred Qualifications: • Associate’s Degree in an ag-related field; or a combination of education, experience and training • Valid Driver’s License Position Summary: This position works under the direction of the Tifton FRS Superintendent and the Tifton ADS Senior Farm Manager to jointly provide leadership and oversight of farm operations at the Alapaha Range Grazing Station. The Animal Facilities Supervisor is responsible for meeting the forage production needs (corn silage, summer annuals, winter annuals, Bermuda grass hay, ext.) for the Tifton/Alapaha Beef Units. The individual will be responsible for maintaining valid pesticide applicator license for the Georgia Department of Agriculture. The Animal Facilities Supervisor will be responsible for preventative/routine maintenance of equipment at the Alapaha Range Grazing Station and supporting units. This individual will also be responsible for non-routine repairs on equipment located at the Beef Unit and supporting units. This individual will work with the Tifton FRS Superintendent and the Tifton ADS Senior Farm Manager to prioritize repairs and maintenance on equipment and facilities. This individual will have experience in mechanic work. This individual will follow written protocol while assisting in research trials and will assist research technicians when utilizing farm assets. Knowledge, Skills, Abilities and/or Competencies: • Farm/Livestock experience • Competent in feed-based row crop production • Knowledge of forage and row-crop management practices and agronomic practices for growing and harvesting crops required for the feeding and maintenance of beef cattle. • Ability to organize and prioritize work activities involved in a beef farm operation and those involved in forage production and field research work. • Ability to implement and conduct research field trials under the direction of research scientists and the Tifton ADS Senior Farm Manager. • Ability to maintain the necessary research and beef management records as specified by research scientists and the Tifton ADS Senior Farm Manager. • Ability to communicate effectively both verbally and in writing. • Ability to utilize computer technology including e-mail, excel, and other recordkeeping programs. • Mechanical knowledge and experience Physical Demands: • Lift, push and carry up to 75 pounds. • Bend, stoop and climb • Work in environmental extremes and outdoor conditions including heat, cold, wet. • Work with hand and arm dexterity. • Work around livestock including dust, noise, smells, etc. • Work varied schedules according to the needs of the farm. May need to work some evenings, weekends, and holidays to ensure maintenance of the herd. • Drive Is driving a responsibility of this position?: Yes Is this a Position of Trust?: Yes Does this position have operation, access, or control of financial resources?: No Does this position require a P-Card? : No Is having a P-Card an essential function of this position? : No Does this position have direct interaction or care of children under the age of 18 or direct patient care?: No Does this position have Security Access (e.g., public safety, IT security, personnel records, patient records, or access to chemicals and medications): Yes Credit and P-Card policy: Be advised a credit check will be required for all positions with financial responsibilities. For additional information about the credit check criteria, visit the UGA Credit Background Check website. Duties/Responsibilities: • Feeding and health care of beef cattle associated with grazing/nutritional research studies including data collection and general livestock production • Routine preventative health care (vaccine injections, parasite control, etc.) and active health care (difficult calving, injury, blood sampling, etc.) Under the direction of the Tifton ADS Senior Farm Manager, works with the institutional animal care to ensure the proper care of animals on the farm • Assisting with weighing/identifying all-beef calves born annually. • Assisting with data collection in support of livestock research projects, which may include forage sampling, weighing cattle and collecting other samples as required. Percentage of time: 50 Duties/Responsibilities: • Participate in planning, organizing and implementing the daily operation of the Alapaha Range Grazing Station. • Maintains daily field records in an organized and accessible format. Submitting land utilization records each year. • Keeps the Tifton ADS Senior Farm Manager and Research Scientists apprised of current and anticipated status of research and field work and makes recommendations for changes or adjustments when necessary. • Carries out experimental procedures without the direct supervision of Research Scientists as determined in research protocols. • Oversees the maintenance and appearance of facilities, machinery, and equipment. • Determines the needs of shop supplies, fuel, oil, fertilizer, pesticides, and animal health supplies and submits recommendations to Tifton FRS Superintendent and Tifton ADS Senior Farm Manager. • Assist with land preparation, planting, managing, and sampling forage plots according to research protocol. • Forage production for cattle, including the establishment of pastures, producing forage or grazing and hay production (mowing, baling, and transporting hay) Percentage of time: 40 Duties/Responsibilities: • Provides effective communication within and outside of the UGA system, including with producers and general public, assists in planning farm visits by various stakeholders including industry clientele, hosting field days for local community groups, visiting faculty, etc. • Comply with all UGA/USG policies including record keeping, timekeeping, training, etc. • Other duties and responsibilities as assigned. Percentage of time: 10 Contact Details: For questions concerning this position or recruitment progression, please refer to the Recruitment Contact listed below. Recruitment Contact Name: Andy Carter Recruitment Contact Email: andyc@uga.edu', '2022-06-03 00:00:00', 'Georgia', '20.0', 'Part Time', '2022-06-03 00:00:00', 'Job Poster', 'web.com', 'company.com', 'It is a long established fact that a reader will b...', 'assets/img/icon/job-list1.png'),
