('117.0', 'Market Research Intern', '2500usd', 'https://careers.ucb.com/global/en/job/79526/Market-Research-Intern?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic', 'Make your mark for patients. We’re here because we want to build the future and transform patients’ lives for the better At UCB, our people are our experiences and achievements, our passion and drive. That’s why we’re looking for talented individuals with diverse backgrounds and experiences - not just the best and brightest, but those who care about making a meaningful difference in the lives of patients. We promote an environment of diversity, openness, and respect where people can make valuable contributions. An exciting journey lies ahead. Will you join us in pushing the boundaries of what’s possible? UCB\'s Market Insights Team is looking for a motivated summer Market Research Intern who is ready to apply knowledge of marketing and market research practices and processes in a fast paced, real world environment. Our market research internship is a paid full-time (May-Aug) learning experience at our Atlanta headquarters where you will be immersed in the daily environment of a leading biopharmaceutical company. How you will contribute: The intern will assist in conducting research, managing projects, analyzing information, writing reports, drafting presentations, and providing recommendations in response to marketing needs. Our company has a broad portfolio of pharmaceutical products in competitive markets. We will provide education in marketing, market research, competitive strategy, and project management to interns of all levels. This is an exciting opportunity for young professionals, especially for those looking to develop skills in the pharmaceutical industry. This paid internship is currently expected to run mid-May and continue through early August 2022. Estimated close to 40hrs per week can be flexible down to a minimum of 20 hours per week. A company laptop and 